727264f-b.text:
Little Neck Parkway, east side, in line of Eighty-third Avenue. This is a set of three views showing a house occupied by Mrs. Remsen in 1873, and P. Hanlon from 1891 to 1909. The outbuildings do not show in the 1928 Atlas of Queens. This house will have to be moved
or demolished when Eighty-third Ave. is extended.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
